<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-28T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-28T13:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.348 Z 4/45: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-28T19:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">September 28,
                                        1923—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>393. Reference Department’s unnumbered despatch of September 18, flight
                            of Zeppelin to New Jersey.</p>
                        <p>Before action is taken on instruction referred to, may I suggest that
                            from here the safer course and one less likely to raise difficulties <pb facs="0265" n="171" xml:id="pg_171"/> would be to wait until the
                            route is definitely determined and then to approach the Government or
                            Governments concerned, taking the attitude of assuming as a matter of
                            course that as necessary consequence of Allied Powers having consented
                            to construction of our Zeppelin, authorization for its flight will be
                            given.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>